@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

 @{b}Installation@{ub}
  1. if MUI v3.3 or highter is not installed, install it.
  2. if MCCMailtext is not installed, Install it (included in this archive)
  3. Use MUIReaderX installer to install MUIReaderX
  4. Run MUIReaderX and a default config will be created.
  5. Configure MUIReaderX (Preferences/General)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Menus" "Menus"

 @{b}Menu Functions@{ub}
   [Project]
   - Update          = Saves Userdata and MailBox to disk
   - Iconify         = Iconify Application
   - CheckMail       = Checks for new mail and adds it to your mailbox
   - About           = Shows About Window
   - About MUI       = Shows About MUI Window
   - Quit            = Quits MUIReaderX

   [Move]
   - Sections List   = Shows SectionList Window + contents
   - Messages List   = Shows MessageList Window + contents
   - ReplyLinks List = Shows LinkList Window + contents
   - MailBox List    = Shows MailBoxList Window + contents
   - Prev            = Previous Message
   - Next            = Next Message

   [Messages]
   - Write           = Writes a new message
   - Reply           = Replies a messages
   - CrossReply      = Replies a message into an other section
   - Forward         = Forwards a Message to an other Section
   - Catchup         = Catchup Current Section
   - CatchupAll      = Catchup All Sections
   - Delete          = Delete Message from MessageBase
   - Save            = Save Message to disk
   - Add To MaiBox   = Adds Message to MailBox
   - Add To Userlist = Adds User (FROM) to Userlist

   [Preferences]
   - Use Signature   = Use defined signature (YES/NO)
   - StripFidoLines  = Strip FidoLine cq Kludges (YES/NO)
   - UserList        = Shows UserList Preferences Window
   - General         = Shows General Preferences Window
   - MUI             = Shows MUI Preferences Window
   - Save Userlist   = Saves UserList to disk
   - Save Settings   = Saves MUIReaderX settings to disk

   [Arexx]
   - Execute Script  = Executes an Arexx script in the background
@ENDNODE

@NODE "KeyBoard" "KeyBoard"

 @{b}KeyBoard@{ub}
  LEFT CURSOR  = Previous Message
  RIGHT CURSOR = Next Message
  UP CURSOR    = Scrolls Message up
  DOWN CURSOS  = Scrolls Message Down
  SPACE        = Next NEW Message or Section.
  F1           = Shows Sections List Window + contents
  F2           = Shows Messages List Window + contents
  F3           = Shows ReplyLinks List Window + contents
  F4           = Shows MailBox List Window + contents
  ECS          = Close Window
@ENDNODE

@NODE "tooltypes" ToolTypes"

 @{b}ToolTypes@{ub}
 MUIReaderX knows seven tooltypes. The following Tooltypes are known by MUIReaderX:

   - CONFIG = (Location Config File)
   - ICONIFY_ICON = (Location Iconify Icon)  {Don't append .info}
   - NEWMAIL_ICON = (Location NewMail Icon)  {Don't append .info}
   - OPENSECTIONLIST = Open SectionList window at startup (FALSE/TRUE)
   - OPENMESSAGELIST = Open MessageList window at startup (FALSE/TRUE)
   - OPENREPLYLINKSLIST = Open ReplyLinksList window at startup (FALSE/TRUE)
   - OPENMAILBOXLIST = Open MailBoxList window at startup (FALSE/TRUE)

  Default Internal Values:

       +-------------------------------------------+
       |  CONFIG = MUIReaderX.config               |
       |  ICONIFY_ICON = Icons/MUIReaderX_Iconify  |
       |  NEWMAIL_ICON = Icons/MUIReaderX_NewMail  |
       |  OPENSECTIONLIST = FALSE                  |
       |  OPENMESSAGELIST = FALSE                  |
       |  OPENREPLYLINKSLIST = FALSE               |
       |  OPENMAILBOXLIST = FALSE                  |
       +-------------------------------------------+  
@ENDNODE

