@NODE "SectionList" "Move/Sections List"

  @{b}Move/Sections List@{ub}
  You can activate the Sections List Window with RIGHT AMIGA S or select it from the Messages menu. The Section Window consists of four coloms (Section / SectionName / Low/High / New) and shows a list of Sections. Which Sections it shows is determind by the Section Mode. Four Section Modes are now supported:

   - @{"All Sections" link "All Sections"}
   - @{"User Sections" link "User Sections"}
   - @{"Unread All Sections" link "Unread All Sections"}
   - @{"Unread User Sections" link "Unread User Sections"}

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA S@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "All Sections" "Move/Sections List/All Sections"

  @{fg Highlight}Move/SectionList/All Sections@{fg text}
   Shows ALL Sections know to xenolink
@ENDNODE

@NODE "User Sections" "Move/Sections List/User Sections"

  @{fg Highlight}Move/SectionList/User Sections@{fg text}
   Shows only Sections that are configured in @{"Preferences/Sections" link Pref_Sections}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unread All Sections" "Move/Sections List/Unread All Sections"

  @{fg Highlight}Move/SectionList/Unread All Sections@{fg text}
   Shows ALL Sections know to xenolink that contain UNREAD messages
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unread User Sections" "Move/Sections List/Unread User Sections"

  @{fg Highlight}Move/SectionList/Unread User Sections@{fg text}
   Shows only Sections that are configured in @{"Preferences/Sections" link Pref_Sections} that contain UNREAD messages
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MessageList" "Move/Messages List"

  @{b}Move/Messages List@{ub}
  You can activate the MessageList Window with RIGHT AMIGA M or select it from the Messages menu. In this window you can see a list of all messages that are present in the Section. You can also select a message you want to read.

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA M@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "LinkedList" "Move/ReplyLinks List"

  @{b}Move/ReplyLinks List@{ub}
  You can activate the LinkList Window with RIGHT AMIGA L or select it from the Messages menu. In this window you can see a list of all linked message (replies and original message). You can also select a message you want to read.

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA L@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MailBox" "Move/MailBox List"

  @{b}Move/MailBox List@{ub}
  You can activate the MailBoxList Window with RIGHT AMIGA B or select it from the Messages menu. In this window you can see a list of messages that are in your private message box. All waitingmail messages will me moved to this Private MailBox. If this window is open, them the Next/Previous message command applies to the Mailbox List. Private MailBox is saved to your Xenolink User Directory. (eg XUSER:Robin_Vermaat/MUIReaderX.mailbox)

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA B@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Previous" "Move/Previous"

  @{b}Move/Previous@{ub}
  Display Previous Messages of selected Secton or MailBox.

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA ,@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Next" "Move/Next"

  @{b}Move/Next@{ub}
  Display Next Messages of selected Secton or MailBox.

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: RAMIGA ,@{uu}
@ENDNODE

