@NODE "Use Signature" "Preferences/Use Signature"

  @{b}Preferences/Use Signature@{ub}
  This menu option enables/disables the use of Signatures (Globaly). This option defaults at the moment to Enable Signature.
  
  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: None@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "StripFidoLines" "Preferences/StripFidoLines"

  @{b}Preferences/StripFidoLines@{ub}
  This menu option enables/disables Xenolink's StripFidoLines (Show Kludges Yes/No). This option defaults at the moment to Enable StripFidoLines.

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: None@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "UserList" "Prefereces/UserList"

  @{b}Preferences/UserList@{ub}
  You can activate the UserEditor Window with selecting it from the Preference menu. With the usereditor you can create a database of your favourite users. You can access this database from the Header Window (when you write or reply a message). User DataBase is saved to the Xenolink User Directory (eg. XUSER:Robin_Vermaat/MUIReaderX.users)

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: None@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "general" "Preferences/General"

  @{b}Preferences/General@{ub}
  You can activate the General Preference Window from the Preferences menu. The preference window consists of five parts, namely:

      - @{" Sections " link Pref_Sections}
      - @{" General  " link Pref_General}
      - @{" Text     " link Pref_Text}
      - @{" Internet " link Pref_Internet}
      - @{" Arexx "    link Pref_Arexx}

  @{u}Keyboard short-cut: None@{uu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Pref_Sections" "Preferences/General/Sections"

  @{fg Highlight}Preferences/General/Sections:@{fg text}
  Here you can Add/Delete Sections to the user definable Section List. Adding multiply sections is permitted. When you created your own private section list (User Sections) you can define which definable text string you want to attach to each section.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Pref_General" "Preferences/General/General"

  @{fg Highlight}Preferences/General/General:@{fg text}
  SysopName     : The xenolink user name who reads the messages.
  Edit          : The external to run (ed or CED -keepio or ed -sticky).
  TagLine       : The TagLine file you want to use.
  Output Window : Standard AmigaDOS Output Window (CON:....)
  Section Mode  : Default Section Mode.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Pref_Text" "Preferences/General/Text"

  @{fg Highlight}Preferences/General/Text:@{fg text}
  ReplyText   : Define Reply Text Header
  ForwardText : Define Forward Text Header
  CrossText   : Define CrossReply Text Header
  SaveText    : Define Save Text Header
  HeaderLeft  : Define MUIReaderX Message Header (Left)
  HeaderRight : Define MUIReaderX Message Header (Right)

  When you define these six different headers you can use symbols like &N, &A etc. Below you can see a list of all known symbols.

       &A = Full Section Name
       &a = Section Number

       &F = Full name Message Writer (FROM)
       &f = First name Message Writer (FROM)
       &O = Fidonet nodenumber Message Writer (FROM)

       &T = Full name addressee of original message (TO)
       &t = First name addressee of original message (TO)
       &o = Fidonet nodenumber addressee of original message (TO)

       &s = Subject of message

       &D = Date of send message
       &M = Time of send message
       &d = Date of received message
       &m = Time of received message

       &N = Newline
       && = & character

       &L = Low Message Number of currect Section
       &H = High Message Number of current Section
       &C = Current Message Number of current Section
       &E = New Message Left in current Section
       &G = Message Flags
       &R = Message Replies

  When you define the two different messages headers you can use different formating and color symbols. Below you can see a list of all symbols known to MUI text objects.

       &-   = Disable text engine.
       &u   = Set the soft style to underline.
       &b   = Set the soft style to bold.
       &i   = Set the soft style to italic.
       &n   = Set the soft style back to normal.
       &<n> = Use pen number n (2..9) as front pen.
       &c   = Center current (and following) line(s).
       &r   = Right justify current (and following) line(s).
       &l   = Left justify current (and following) line(s).

  @{b}@{i}NOTE: Don't create Headers that are bigger than 1KB (1024 chars)@{ub}@{ui}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Pref_Internet" "Preferences/General/Internet"

  @{fg Highlight}Preferences/General/Internet:@{fg text}
  Gateway         : FidoNet Address of your gateway (eg. 90:123/100.0)
  EMail Section   : Xenolinks Section Number for Your email (eg. 800)
  Fidonet Address : YOUR Fidonet Address (eg. 90:123/199.0)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Pref_Arexx" "Preferences/General/Arexx"

  @{fg Highlight}Preferences/General/Arexx:@{fg text}
  Here you can add/delete arexx scripts to the MUIReaderX Arexx menu dynamicly. Field you must fill in:

    Menu   -> Menu Name
    Key    -> ShortCut to Arexx Script
    File   -> Arexx Script to execute
    Window -> Should an Output Window be opened ?
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MUI" "Preferences/MUI"

  @{b}Preferences/MUI@{ub}
