  @{b}Arexx Interface/Port@{ub}
   Port: @{fg highlight}MUIREADERX.1@{fg text}
              
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MUICommands" "Arexx Interface/MUI Commands"

  @{b}Arexx Interface/MUI Commands@{ub}
   - @{fg highlight}QUIT [FORCE]@{fg text}
       Ends the application.

   - @{fg highlight}HIDE@{fg text}
       Hides (iconifies) the application

   - @{fg highlight}SHOW@{fg text}
       Shows (pops up) an iconified application.

   - @{fg highlight}INFO ITEM/A@{fg text}
       According to the given parameter the result string is filled with
       the following contents:

          - "title"       Title of the application
          - "author"      Author of the  application
          - "copyright"   Copyright message
          - "description" Short description
          - "version"     Version string
          - "base"        Name of the ARexx port
          - "screen"      Name of the public screen

   - @{fg highlight}HELP FILE/A@{fg text}
       A list of all ARexx commands available for the application is
       written into the given file. In addition to the default commands an
       MUI application can (and of course should) support many application
       specific commands. The help list will contain these commands as
       well.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MRXCommands" "Arexx Interface/MUIReaderX Specific Commands"

  @{b}Arexx Interface/MUIReaderX Specific Commands@{ub}
   - @{fg highlight}ABOUT@{fg text}
       Shows MUIReaderX About Window

   - @{fg highlight}ABOUTMUI@{fg text}
       Shows MUI About Window

   - @{fg highlight}NEXTMESSAGE@{fg text}
       Display Next Message

   - @{fg highlight}PREVIOUSMESSAGE@{fg text}
       Display Previous Message

   - @{fg highlight}SPACEMESSAGE@{fg text}
       Display Next new message or section.

   - @{fg highlight}CATCHUP@{fg text}
       Catchup Current Section

   - @{fg highlight}CATCHUPALL@{fg text}
       Catchup All Sections

   - @{fg highlight}SLEEP@{fg text}
       Puts the application to sleep (locks GUI)

   - @{fg highlight}UNSLEEP@{fg text}
       Awakens the application (unlocks GUI)

   - @{fg highlight}GETMSGDATA ITEM/A@{fg text}
       According to the given parameter the result string is filled with
       the following @{u}current@{uu} message contents:

          - "number"          Message Number
          - "subject"         Message Subject
          - "flags"           Message Flags
          - "replies"         Message Replies (NYI)
          - "data"            Message Data

          - "from_fullname"   Message From FullName
          - "from_nodenumber" Message From NodeNumber
          - "from_date"       Message From Date
          - "from_time"       Message From Time

          - "to_fullname"     Message To FullName
          - "to_nodenumber"   Message To NodeNumber
          - "to_date"         Message To Date
          - "to_time"         Message To Time

   - @{fg highlight}GETSECTIONATA ITEM/A@{fg text}
       According to the given parameter the result string is filled with
       the following @{u}current@{uu} section contents:

          - "section"         Section Number
          - "name"            Section Name
          - "low"             Section Low
          - "high"            Section High
          - "net"             Section Net
          - "type"            Section Type
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ErrorCodes" "Arexx Interface/Error Codes"

  @{b}Arexx Interface/Error Codes@{ub}
  In case of an error, MUIReaderX returns the following values to the rexx script:

   - @{fg highlight}-1@{fg text} : Wrong command definition in host program. Should never happen.
   - @{fg highlight}-2@{fg text} : Out of memory.
   - @{fg highlight}-3@{fg text} : Unknown ARexx command.
   - @{fg highlight}-4@{fg text} : Syntax error.

   - @{fg highlight} 0@{fg text} : Successfull
   - @{fg highlight} 1@{fg text} : Unknown Argument for Arexx Command
   - @{fg highlight} 2@{fg text} : Xenolink Message not found
   - @{fg highlight} 3@{fg text} : Error Saving Message

@ENDNODE

